I'll leave it with you, Timmy.

275
00:19:28,840 --> 00:19:29,840
Bye now.

276
00:19:39,920 --> 00:19:41,000
This way, please, Mr. Golf.

277
00:19:43,760 --> 00:19:45,840
Hello. Are you here for speed dating?

278
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:47,000
Yes.

279
00:19:47,880 --> 00:19:49,800
Please write your name on this sticker tag.

280
00:19:50,720 --> 00:19:51,720
Okay.

281
00:19:51,800 --> 00:19:54,600
Each round lasts five minutes.

282
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:57,000
You'll hear a bell when time's up.

283
00:19:58,560 --> 00:19:59,120
Sure.

284
00:19:59,480 --> 00:20:01,280
All right, Mr. Jack. Please step inside.

285
00:20:01,840 --> 00:20:02,320
Thank you.

286
00:20:02,840 --> 00:20:03,840
Of course.

287
00:20:07,240 --> 00:20:08,240
Hi.

288
00:20:08,520 --> 00:20:09,040
Hi.

289
00:20:09,120 --> 00:20:10,120
You are…?

290
00:20:10,480 --> 00:20:11,480
Jack.

291
00:20:11,640 --> 00:20:12,640
I'm Ton.

292
00:20:13,160 --> 00:20:14,960
What's your MBTI?

293
00:20:15,720 --> 00:20:16,720
INFJ.

294
00:20:19,320 --> 00:20:21,800
I'm ESTP.

295
00:20:22,640 --> 00:20:24,640
We're complete opposites.

296
00:20:36,680 --> 00:20:37,800
You're very good-looking.

297
00:20:38,680 --> 00:20:41,760
You look like my next boyfriend.

298
00:20:44,520 --> 00:20:45,520
Can I have your chat ID?

299
00:20:51,520 --> 00:20:53,240
Sorry, my friend list is full.

300
00:21:03,600 --> 00:21:04,000
Hello.
Hello, Jack.

301
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:07,200
I'm Dean.

302
00:21:12,880 --> 00:21:16,080
I just broke up with my boyfriend.
So now I'm single.

303
00:21:20,760 --> 00:21:21,760
Well?

304
00:21:22,800 --> 00:21:24,240
Already looking for a new boyfriend?

305
00:21:25,480 --> 00:21:31,000
My ex was a piece of shit.
I'm looking for an upgrade.

306
00:21:31,880 --> 00:21:32,880
Is that so?

307
00:21:35,080 --> 00:21:38,160
But I don't think you like anyone here yet.

308
00:21:39,680 --> 00:21:40,680
Just admit it, Jack.

309
00:21:41,200 --> 00:21:43,640
I'm the most compatible with you.

310
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:48,520
There's no point in holding auditions.

311
00:21:49,440 --> 00:21:53,120
The Romeo role is mine. No question.

312
00:21:55,960 --> 00:21:57,000
How would you know…

313
00:21:58,680 --> 00:21:59,760
when I'm the one choosing?

314
00:22:01,040 --> 00:22:04,720
And now I'm choosing
new things for my life.

315
00:22:07,760 --> 00:22:08,760
Why?

316
00:22:10,720 --> 00:22:14,520
Because you were jealous
of Sand and me at the party?

317
00:22:18,840 --> 00:22:20,560
You want my full attention all to yourself?

318
00:22:22,320 --> 00:22:23,720
You just…

319
00:22:25,440 --> 00:22:27,040
think too highly of yourself, as always.

320
00:22:27,240 --> 00:22:28,920
If that's what you think, fine.

321
00:22:31,080 --> 00:22:34,400
I hope you find someone better than me.

322
00:22:35,960 --> 00:22:37,320
As your boyfriend…

323
00:22:39,320 --> 00:22:40,360
and as your actor.

324
00:22:45,680 --> 00:22:49,800
Maybe your era is over, Dean.

325
00:22:51,960 --> 00:22:52,960
Well…

326
00:22:54,960 --> 00:22:57,720
We'll see about that, Jack.

327
00:23:26,680 --> 00:23:28,359
It's our faculty stage play.
Are you interested?

328
00:23:28,360 --> 00:23:29,960
Come to the casting.

329
00:23:30,640 --> 00:23:32,640
It's the play audition. Are you in?

330
00:23:37,720 --> 00:23:38,720
Are you auditioning?

331
00:23:40,240 --> 00:23:42,480
Mm. I think I'll give it a try.

332
00:23:43,920 --> 00:23:44,920
What about you?

333
00:23:46,560 --> 00:23:48,280
I'll stay an accountant. Like always.

334
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:52,560
What role are you auditioning for?
A supporting role?

335
00:23:56,680 --> 00:23:57,680
I'm going for the lead.

336
00:23:59,920 --> 00:24:00,920
Romeo.

337
00:24:02,360 --> 00:24:04,440
Whoa! Raffy!

338
00:24:05,640 --> 00:24:08,360
What's the point?
Jack will always choose Dean.

339
00:24:10,320 --> 00:24:11,480
Maybe not this time.

340
00:24:12,640 --> 00:24:15,560
They broke up. That means I have a shot.

341
00:24:17,160 --> 00:24:20,960
My moment's here. How could I not take it?

342
00:24:28,280 --> 00:24:31,720
I love you, Romeo.
And I will not let you go.

343
00:24:34,640 --> 00:24:39,200
Even if our families are at war,
it doesn't mean we can't love each other.

344
00:24:44,960 --> 00:24:48,280
Hatred can't defy our love, Romeo.

345
00:24:50,360 --> 00:24:51,440
Thank you. Thank you.

346
00:24:51,960 --> 00:24:53,199
Please wait for the results.

347
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:54,200
Please.

348
00:25:03,640 --> 00:25:06,680
Jack, that's ten people already.
No one's caught your heart?

349
00:25:07,200 --> 00:25:08,280
We've been at this all day.

350
00:25:08,440 --> 00:25:09,440
Right.

351
00:25:09,840 --> 00:25:10,920
They're just not right yet.

352
00:25:11,960 --> 00:25:13,000
Not right?

353
00:25:14,360 --> 00:25:17,280
Then stop being stubborn.
Choose Dean and get it over with.

354
00:25:17,840 --> 00:25:18,840
Exactly.

355
00:25:19,040 --> 00:25:21,880
Or if you don't want to sign him up,
Timmy can do it for you.

356
00:25:23,360 --> 00:25:24,360
Hey.

357
00:25:27,640 --> 00:25:28,720
I'm auditioning for Romeo.

358
00:25:48,360 --> 00:25:51,040
Hi, I'm Dean Dechakorn Prempreeda.

359
00:25:51,640 --> 00:25:53,400
Height: 176 centimeters. Weight: 67 kilos.

360
00:25:54,040 --> 00:25:55,560
I'm auditioning for the role of Romeo.

361
00:26:01,360 --> 00:26:02,360
Should I begin?

362
00:26:03,360 --> 00:26:05,680
Or would you like to
know my background first?

363
00:26:07,880 --> 00:26:09,160
Though I doubt that's necessary.

364
00:26:09,600 --> 00:26:14,000
The director knows me down to every pore.

365
00:26:22,160 --> 00:26:23,160
Hey.

366
00:26:25,560 --> 00:26:27,920
Can I join the audition
too? Am I still in time?

367
00:26:28,760 --> 00:26:30,120
Sorry, I took a while to prepare.

368
00:26:32,400 --> 00:26:34,040
What role are you auditioning for, Raffy?

369
00:26:35,480 --> 00:26:36,480
Romeo.

370
00:26:51,560 --> 00:26:55,200
If loving you means
I have to sacrifice and walk away

371
00:26:56,480 --> 00:26:58,000
to make someone else happy,

372
00:27:00,680 --> 00:27:02,040
then that isn't true love.

373
00:27:03,240 --> 00:27:04,400
Because true love…

374
00:27:06,640 --> 00:27:07,880
means burning together.

375
00:27:10,320 --> 00:27:13,680
If you already know how it ends,
why choose the same path again?

376
00:27:16,080 --> 00:27:19,440
You can choose something new.
And you won't regret it.

377
00:27:21,240 --> 00:27:25,440
We built everything together.

378
00:27:26,000 --> 00:27:27,480
Our lives. Our memories.

379
00:27:30,080 --> 00:27:32,240
You can't turn back
and walk away from me, Romeo.

380
00:27:34,720 --> 00:27:39,320
You can live without the others,
but not without me.

381
00:27:41,280 --> 00:27:43,360
I'm not asking you to choose right now.

382
00:27:45,440 --> 00:27:52,840
I just want you to know
I'm ready to stand by your side.

383
00:28:03,240 --> 00:28:05,640
- Just choose me, Romeo.
- Just choose me, Romeo.

384
00:28:22,440 --> 00:28:23,440
So what's up, Jack?

385
00:28:23,720 --> 00:28:24,720
You look stressed.

386
00:28:25,040 --> 00:28:26,920
Can't decide between Dean and Raffy?

387
00:28:27,520 --> 00:28:29,160
I'd be stressed too.

388
00:28:30,520 --> 00:28:34,320
Jack, if you can't
choose, let them both play.

389
00:28:35,760 --> 00:28:37,320
You need two Romeos anyway.

390
00:28:38,040 --> 00:28:39,040
I can't.

391
00:28:39,720 --> 00:28:41,480
Dean and Raffy have the same character.

392
00:28:41,760 --> 00:28:43,720
Between the two, I can choose only one.

393
00:28:44,200 --> 00:28:45,560
What about the other Romeo?

394
00:28:46,080 --> 00:28:48,360
Didn't anyone from casting click for you?

395
00:28:49,920 --> 00:28:50,920
Not yet.

396
00:28:51,440 --> 00:28:52,720
Gosh.

397
00:28:53,680 --> 00:28:56,000
Can you at least make our jobs easier?

398
00:28:57,720 --> 00:28:59,359
Hey, boys.

399
00:28:59,360 --> 00:29:00,680
This one's on the house.

400
00:29:01,160 --> 00:29:04,800
I'm giving you the whole bottle
since you look so grumpy.

401
00:29:05,440 --> 00:29:06,680
Didn't your boyfriend come too?

402
00:29:09,600 --> 00:29:10,600
Who's my boyfriend?

403
00:29:11,280 --> 00:29:11,960
Dean—duh!

404
00:29:12,280 --> 00:29:13,160
Come on, Pink.

405
00:29:13,161 --> 00:29:14,840
Dean's his ex.

406
00:29:15,000 --> 00:29:15,520
They broke up, sis.

407
00:29:15,521 --> 00:29:17,481
Seriously? I didn't know.
I didn't get the update.

408
00:29:17,880 --> 00:29:19,360
I still see you hanging out together.

409
00:29:19,600 --> 00:29:20,600
How nice.

410
00:29:20,800 --> 00:29:23,000
Breaking up but staying
in the same friend group.

411
00:29:23,440 --> 00:29:25,320
I really can't keep up
with Gen Z relationships.

412
00:29:25,720 --> 00:29:26,720
Bye now.

413
00:29:27,760 --> 00:29:28,879
That's because you're old, sis.

414
00:29:28,880 --> 00:29:30,880
Damn you!

415
00:29:32,720 --> 00:29:35,359
If you want people to stop talking

416
00:29:35,360 --> 00:29:36,760
about Dean, you've got two options.

417
00:29:37,360 --> 00:29:40,480
One, stop being friends with him.
Two, get a new boyfriend.

418
00:29:40,800 --> 00:29:42,320
You're exactly right.

419
00:29:42,880 --> 00:29:47,720
But if we're still sitting here,
no one's going to hit on you.

420
00:29:48,640 --> 00:29:49,720
Let's go, Tua.

421
00:29:50,440 --> 00:29:52,520
Give Jack some space.

422
00:29:53,320 --> 00:29:53,920
Come.
Do I have to?

423
00:29:54,561 --> 00:29:55,600
Come with me.

424
00:29:55,960 --> 00:29:59,160
You don't want to be the third wheel.

425
00:30:04,720 --> 00:30:05,720
Hi, Jack.

426
00:30:06,640 --> 00:30:07,840
Why are you sitting all alone?

427
00:30:09,520 --> 00:30:11,280
I don't know where Timmy and Tua went.

428
00:30:11,800 --> 00:30:13,600
What about you? Did you come alone?

429
00:30:14,440 --> 00:30:16,680
I'm meeting Pete, but he's not here yet.

430
00:30:16,960 --> 00:30:19,240
Mind if I sit with you for now?

431
00:30:20,480 --> 00:30:21,480
Sure.

432
00:30:27,400 --> 00:30:32,680
And don't ask about the casting.
I haven't decided yet.

433
00:30:36,040 --> 00:30:39,360
How was it, though? Was I okay?

434
00:30:40,920 --> 00:30:42,720
I'm not very confident.

435
00:30:43,040 --> 00:30:45,720
Hey, your acting has improved a lot.

436
00:30:46,320 --> 00:30:47,320
I liked it.

437
00:30:50,080 --> 00:30:53,120
Can you say that again? Let me record it.

438
00:30:53,360 --> 00:30:54,816
It's not every day
I get a compliment from you.

439
00:30:54,840 --> 00:30:55,440
You're exaggerating.
Hey.

440
00:30:58,680 --> 00:31:00,480
I wasn't sure if you liked it.

441
00:31:01,480 --> 00:31:03,680
I really want to work
with someone as capable as you.

442
00:31:08,840 --> 00:31:09,880
I want to be your muse.

443
00:31:19,040 --> 00:31:20,120
Don't you have friends?

444
00:31:21,160 --> 00:31:22,160
Is that why you're here?

445
00:31:27,480 --> 00:31:28,600
I was waiting for my friend.

446
00:31:29,200 --> 00:31:30,680
Jack was alone too.

447
00:31:33,880 --> 00:31:37,920
Hey, we never got to act together.

448
00:31:39,000 --> 00:31:43,360
I want to play with you, but it's a shame
we auditioned for the same role.

449
00:31:45,040 --> 00:31:46,280
Maybe we will.

450
00:31:46,480 --> 00:31:51,840
I'll be the main character,
and you'll be ensemble, like always.

451
00:31:54,360 --> 00:31:55,360
Dean!

452
00:31:58,200 --> 00:31:59,200
That's fine.

453
00:32:00,520 --> 00:32:02,000
You're actually my idol.

454
00:32:03,360 --> 00:32:04,440
I want to be like you.

455
00:32:05,360 --> 00:32:09,560
Whatever you had before, I want that too.

456
00:32:20,560 --> 00:32:23,320
I think I should go.
I'll see you later, Jack.

457
00:32:35,120 --> 00:32:37,520
I admire his effort.

458
00:32:37,960 --> 00:32:39,560
He's been after you since freshman year.

459
00:32:40,320 --> 00:32:42,160
You rejected him and chose me instead.

460
00:32:42,680 --> 00:32:44,520
And he's still chasing
you in our fourth year.

461
00:32:46,120 --> 00:32:49,120
Mm. But maybe it's not too late.

462
00:32:51,160 --> 00:32:52,480
Are you giving him the lead role?

463
00:32:55,400 --> 00:32:56,400
Maybe.

464
00:32:57,760 --> 00:32:59,520
The audience might
want to see something new.

465
00:33:00,240 --> 00:33:01,600
The old thing is predictable.

466
00:33:02,560 --> 00:33:03,560
Boring.

467
00:33:25,000 --> 00:33:26,920
Hey, we meet again.

468
00:33:31,920 --> 00:33:32,920
Did you follow me?

469
00:33:34,360 --> 00:33:36,400
Seriously, are you hitting on me?

470
00:33:37,480 --> 00:33:38,800
If you are, don't.

471
00:33:39,280 --> 00:33:40,280
It's a waste of time.

472
00:33:40,360 --> 00:33:43,000
Cocky much? I'm a DJ here.

473
00:33:45,640 --> 00:33:49,800
Then don't say hi next time.

474
00:33:50,520 --> 00:33:52,680
I don't make friends with one-night stands.

475
00:33:54,720 --> 00:33:56,840
Was I that bad
you don't want anyone to know?

476
00:34:02,360 --> 00:34:03,520
I think I did pretty well.

477
00:34:04,840 --> 00:34:06,560
How did you sound that night again?

478
00:34:10,880 --> 00:34:12,000
Don't try.

479
00:34:12,600 --> 00:34:13,760
I have high standards.

480
00:34:14,240 --> 00:34:15,280
You don't meet them.

481
00:34:17,520 --> 00:34:18,760
Are you sure they are high?

482
00:34:19,520 --> 00:34:23,320
We talked for less than
five minutes and you already gave in.

483
00:34:25,040 --> 00:34:28,920
You know what,
you don't have to play hard to get.

484
00:34:29,840 --> 00:34:31,200
It doesn't make you more valuable.

485
00:34:38,160 --> 00:34:39,720
Don't flatter yourself.

486
00:34:40,520 --> 00:34:44,000
You were just in the right place
at the right time…

487
00:34:45,840 --> 00:34:47,520
and right for my mood.

488
00:34:55,680 --> 00:34:57,480
Whoo!

489
00:35:00,480 --> 00:35:02,480
Tua, what's the casting result?

490
00:35:02,640 --> 00:35:03,640
Did Jack choose me?

491
00:35:04,760 --> 00:35:06,440
You don't have it easy this time.

492
00:35:06,760 --> 00:35:09,519
We have to admit Raffy's improved a lot.

493
00:35:09,520 --> 00:35:11,559
Raffy? Please.

494
00:35:11,560 --> 00:35:14,079
I can control my tears.
Want them from the left eye or the right?

495
00:35:14,080 --> 00:35:15,920
Inner corner or outer
corner? I can do it all.

496
00:35:16,160 --> 00:35:16,760
I know.

497
00:35:16,761 --> 00:35:18,840
No one's questioning your talent, Dean.

498
00:35:19,280 --> 00:35:22,600
But Jack might be worried you'll
mess up his play again like last year.

499
00:35:23,120 --> 00:35:24,920
You overslept and didn't make it on time.

500
00:35:25,880 --> 00:35:26,880
Fine.

501
00:35:28,680 --> 00:35:33,840
And another concern right now
is the other Romeo.

502
00:35:34,120 --> 00:35:35,880
No one seems to be
catching Jack's attention.

503
00:35:44,720 --> 00:35:45,720
Hey.

504
00:35:46,160 --> 00:35:47,480
Arnold works here too?

505
00:35:49,760 --> 00:35:51,800
Yeah. Pink just recruited him.

506
00:35:57,840 --> 00:35:59,880
Whoever ends up as
his partner is going to be lucky.

507
00:36:00,600 --> 00:36:02,680
He's hot and hardworking.

508
00:36:04,240 --> 00:36:05,240
He's versatile.

509
00:36:09,760 --> 00:36:10,760
Don't you think?

510
00:36:12,840 --> 00:36:13,840
I don't know.

511
00:36:15,160 --> 00:36:18,200
Come on, Tua. If you like him, go for it.

512
00:36:18,560 --> 00:36:20,496
Can't you see how many people
are making eyes at him?

513
00:36:20,520 --> 00:36:21,880
Someone else might grab him first.

514
00:36:34,800 --> 00:36:35,800
Oh, hey, Tua.

515
00:36:36,240 --> 00:36:37,320
You're here too?

516
00:36:37,960 --> 00:36:39,880
I came with Dean and Jack.

517
00:36:40,400 --> 00:36:41,400
Are you drunk?

518
00:36:41,960 --> 00:36:42,960
Drunk? Come on.

519
00:36:44,680 --> 00:36:45,560
Good then.

520
00:36:45,640 --> 00:36:48,040
Don't get drunk too fast.
I can't give you a ride home.

521
00:36:48,680 --> 00:36:49,680
Still on the clock.

522
00:36:52,240 --> 00:36:55,040
Oh, hey, are you interested in
joining our faculty play?

523
00:36:56,280 --> 00:36:57,280
Me?

524
00:36:58,840 --> 00:36:59,920
Come on, I can't act.

525
00:37:00,200 --> 00:37:01,600
Dancing, that I can work with.

526
00:37:01,640 --> 00:37:04,000
I actually think you'd be perfect.

527
00:37:04,160 --> 00:37:06,520
You've got the right look, Arnold.

528
00:37:07,480 --> 00:37:09,240
You look like someone Jack would want.

529
00:37:11,760 --> 00:37:12,920
Um… I don't think so.

530
00:37:13,440 --> 00:37:16,440
If I spend time rehearsing,
I'll lose out on work and money.

531
00:37:20,360 --> 00:37:22,840
I think it doesn't hurt to try.

532
00:37:23,960 --> 00:37:26,720
If you get the role, you'll get paid too.

533
00:37:27,000 --> 00:37:28,040
I will?

534
00:37:28,560 --> 00:37:30,680
It's around 20,000.

535
00:37:38,200 --> 00:37:40,240
Hmm. Let me sleep on it.

536
00:37:41,280 --> 00:37:42,280
Thanks for asking anyway.

537
00:37:48,160 --> 00:37:49,280
Here, a freebie for you.

538
00:37:49,600 --> 00:37:50,640
Don't tell Pink.

539
00:37:51,320 --> 00:37:52,559
And don't get drunk too fast.

540
00:37:52,560 --> 00:37:53,560
Yeah.

541
00:37:54,680 --> 00:37:55,680
Thank you, man.

542
00:38:03,080 --> 00:38:04,080
I came prepared.

543
00:38:06,040 --> 00:38:07,280
I mean… financially.

544
00:38:10,560 --> 00:38:12,200
Whoo!

545
00:38:12,560 --> 00:38:14,320
Cheers!

546
00:38:34,240 --> 00:38:35,560
I'm stepping out for a cigarette.

547
00:38:35,680 --> 00:38:38,120
Hey, your glass is still full.
Where are you going?

548
00:38:46,680 --> 00:38:47,680
Watch the booth for me.

549
00:38:51,160 --> 00:38:52,160
Hey, Jack.

550
00:38:54,600 --> 00:38:55,600
Are you drunk yet?

551
00:38:55,960 --> 00:38:56,960
Not yet.

552
00:38:57,840 --> 00:38:58,040
So...

553
00:38:58,041 --> 00:38:59,240
You hardly ever come home.

554
00:39:03,320 --> 00:39:04,520
I've been busy.

555
00:39:05,520 --> 00:39:06,800
Working on the play.

556
00:39:08,120 --> 00:39:09,600
Mom keeps asking about you.

557
00:39:12,240 --> 00:39:13,320
Is this your new boyfriend?

558
00:39:13,760 --> 00:39:14,320
What a hotshot you are.

559
00:39:14,440 --> 00:39:15,480
Boyfriend, my ass.

560
00:39:15,880 --> 00:39:17,000
He's my friend.

561
00:39:17,280 --> 00:39:19,040
Hey! Just a friend?

562
00:39:19,840 --> 00:39:21,640
I thought you were
already seeing someone new.

563
00:39:24,080 --> 00:39:25,520
What the hell are you talking about?

564
00:39:34,240 --> 00:39:35,240
Are they siblings?

565
00:39:37,400 --> 00:39:38,760
No one in the faculty knows.

566
00:39:39,400 --> 00:39:40,880
Most people don't know we're related.

567
00:39:41,560 --> 00:39:43,440
It's not like I'm eager
to call him my big bro.

568
00:40:04,000 --> 00:40:06,120
Excuse me. Can I borrow your lighter?

569
00:40:07,320 --> 00:40:08,440
I didn't bring one.

570
00:40:23,880 --> 00:40:25,760
Are those glasses for poor eyesight?

571
00:40:27,600 --> 00:40:28,960
How short-sighted are you?

572
00:40:31,360 --> 00:40:32,360
Three hundred.

573
00:40:33,680 --> 00:40:35,360
Can you see clearly without them?

574
00:40:38,280 --> 00:40:42,440
I mean, how close would I have to be
for you to see me clearly?

575
00:40:56,320 --> 00:40:58,680
Whoo!

576
00:41:09,040 --> 00:41:10,920
Why didn't you tell me
you're Jack's brother?

577
00:41:11,960 --> 00:41:12,960
What?

578
00:41:13,080 --> 00:41:15,560
I asked why you didn't tell me
you're Jack's brother.

579
00:41:16,040 --> 00:41:17,360
The exact reason you're thinking.

580
00:41:18,760 --> 00:41:19,760
Why?

581
00:41:20,040 --> 00:41:21,040
Do you like him?

582
00:41:24,000 --> 00:41:25,280
Oh.

583
00:41:26,040 --> 00:41:31,000
Are you scared that if Jack
finds out we hooked up, he won't want you?

584
00:41:33,640 --> 00:41:34,680
Do not tell him.

585
00:41:35,840 --> 00:41:36,560
Who knows?

586
00:41:36,561 --> 00:41:38,320
I might let it slip when I'm drunk.

587
00:41:38,640 --> 00:41:40,240
Asshole. I said don't tell him.

588
00:41:43,800 --> 00:41:44,880
What do I get in return?

589
00:41:46,040 --> 00:41:47,240
Are you blackmailing me?

590
00:41:48,400 --> 00:41:50,280
Shit! Shit! I'm sorry.

591
00:41:52,560 --> 00:41:53,560
I'm sorry.

592
00:41:54,080 --> 00:41:55,120
Just leave.

593
00:41:55,360 --> 00:41:56,360
What's going on here?

594
00:41:56,800 --> 00:41:58,079
You're killing the vibe for my customers.

595
00:41:58,080 --> 00:41:59,000
Fix it now.

596
00:41:59,025 --> 00:42:00,258
I'll handle the problem.

597
00:42:00,560 --> 00:42:01,560
Then handle it.

598
00:42:02,840 --> 00:42:04,280
Give us a second, guys.

599
00:42:04,480 --> 00:42:06,600
Boo!

600
00:42:07,040 --> 00:42:08,560
Hang tight. The music's coming back.

601
00:42:11,080 --> 00:42:11,640
It's done, sis.

602
00:42:11,641 --> 00:42:13,000
Okay, let's get back to the fun.

603
00:42:17,560 --> 00:42:18,920
How should I make it up?

604
00:42:23,800 --> 00:42:24,800
Don't worry.

605
00:42:25,160 --> 00:42:26,440
You will surely get your chance.

606
00:42:35,360 --> 00:42:36,480
Keep walking.

607
00:42:39,360 --> 00:42:41,280
Hey, Timmy, don't puke.

608
00:42:42,480 --> 00:42:45,560
Of course I won't. Don't you worry.

609
00:42:47,360 --> 00:42:50,200
Hey, where are Jack and Dean?

610
00:42:51,120 --> 00:42:52,880
Worry about yourself, Timmy.

611
00:42:53,840 --> 00:42:55,280
Jack bailed and went home.

612
00:42:55,720 --> 00:42:57,480
Dean left with someone.

613
00:42:57,600 --> 00:43:00,360
Hey, hey.

614
00:43:10,000 --> 00:43:11,520
Hey, Tua.

615
00:43:13,040 --> 00:43:14,040
Timmy, wow.

616
00:43:16,200 --> 00:43:17,200
You're done?

617
00:43:18,680 --> 00:43:20,320
Here, let me help.

618
00:43:20,720 --> 00:43:21,720
Gosh. He's out of it.

619
00:43:22,640 --> 00:43:23,800
How are you two getting home?

620
00:43:24,680 --> 00:43:27,920
I'll book a ride and send him home first.

621
00:43:28,920 --> 00:43:30,560
You're such a good friend, Tua.

622
00:43:31,600 --> 00:43:32,680
Here, I'll give you a hand.

623
00:43:32,720 --> 00:43:33,720
Timmy.

624
00:43:34,640 --> 00:43:35,240
Timmy.

625
00:43:35,560 --> 00:43:36,920
When did you get taller?

626
00:43:37,960 --> 00:43:41,600
Tua, about the play you mentioned earlier…

627
00:43:42,280 --> 00:43:43,280
I'm in.

628
00:43:43,520 --> 00:43:45,200
I don't know if I'll get the part, though.

629
00:43:45,800 --> 00:43:47,320
You will.

630
00:43:47,600 --> 00:43:48,600
I believe you will.

631
00:43:48,880 --> 00:43:49,560
I'll try.

632
00:43:49,880 --> 00:43:51,160
Come on. Let's get Timmy home.

633
00:43:53,240 --> 00:43:54,240
Thanks a lot.

634
00:43:54,720 --> 00:43:55,799
It's my job to take care of customers.

635
00:43:55,800 --> 00:43:56,840
Hey, I'm fine.

636
00:44:33,680 --> 00:44:34,840
How did you get in?

637
00:44:35,880 --> 00:44:39,600
You're still using
my birthday as your passcode.

638
00:44:44,640 --> 00:44:46,600
Sorry for cockblocking.

639
00:44:50,000 --> 00:44:51,600
But for my replacement,

640
00:44:53,280 --> 00:44:54,600
this is the best you could find?

641
00:44:58,400 --> 00:44:59,200
Are you drunk?

642
00:44:59,320 --> 00:45:01,240
If you are, go home.
Why are you even here?

643
00:45:01,640 --> 00:45:02,720
Why can't I?

644
00:45:03,440 --> 00:45:04,560
I used to live here.

645
00:45:05,400 --> 00:45:06,400
This bed…

646
00:45:08,520 --> 00:45:09,960
we used to have sex all the time.

647
00:45:11,520 --> 00:45:12,520
Well?

648
00:45:13,480 --> 00:45:17,880
Did you miss me so much
you had to find my replacement?

649
00:45:19,440 --> 00:45:23,480
I don't know what your deal is,
but I'm stepping out of this.

650
00:45:30,840 --> 00:45:31,840
What do you want?

651
00:45:31,880 --> 00:45:33,000
Say it and leave.

652
00:45:35,680 --> 00:45:37,120
Why are you so mean to me?

653
00:45:37,760 --> 00:45:41,000
It's two in the morning.
Can't I crash here?

654
00:45:41,360 --> 00:45:42,360
No.

655
00:45:43,080 --> 00:45:45,720
Why don't you sleep with
the guy you were flirting with at the bar?

656
00:45:48,120 --> 00:45:49,840
I was flirting just for fun.

657
00:45:55,040 --> 00:46:02,640
But tonight… I'd rather be with you.

658
00:46:15,400 --> 00:46:17,920
Do you want the role so bad
you're willing to trade your body?

659
00:46:18,720 --> 00:46:19,240
Huh?

660
00:46:19,720 --> 00:46:20,720
Mm.

661
00:46:22,320 --> 00:46:23,520
I want the role.

662
00:46:25,760 --> 00:46:27,160
And I want you too.

663
00:46:29,160 --> 00:46:34,880
You know I deserve that role
without even auditioning.

664
00:46:36,240 --> 00:46:37,880
Your method won't work.

665
00:46:42,800 --> 00:46:44,240
We won't know

666
00:46:45,400 --> 00:46:46,520
unless we try. Right?

667
00:47:00,880 --> 00:47:02,120
Can I audition again?

668
00:47:03,480 --> 00:47:05,080
I'll prove to you

669
00:47:07,120 --> 00:47:08,720
who's the most suitable for the role.

670
00:47:39,120 --> 00:47:40,840
Just exes hooking up.

671
00:47:42,600 --> 00:47:44,160
Whatever floats your boat.

672
00:48:12,840 --> 00:48:16,079
(Next Episode)
And the roles of Romeo go to…

673
00:48:16,080 --> 00:48:17,120
Nice work.

674
00:48:17,400 --> 00:48:19,440
Sneaking your crush into the project.

675
00:48:19,560 --> 00:48:22,680
If you like him that much, try kissing him.

676
00:48:23,080 --> 00:48:24,680
Why don't you try that kiss with me?

677
00:48:27,320 --> 00:48:28,736
I don't mind if you move
on with someone else…

678
00:48:28,760 --> 00:48:32,240
as long as it's not Raffy.

679
00:48:32,640 --> 00:48:33,640
Scared of losing?

680
00:48:34,960 --> 00:48:35,800
How about this, Rome?

681
00:48:35,880 --> 00:48:37,920
I'll serve him up for you.

682
00:48:38,200 --> 00:48:39,840
Whether you take him or not is your call.
